    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2005-02-01</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2005-02-28T21:46:04Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Ruben Estrella-Soto Act of 2005 - Directs the Secretary of the military department concerned to provide an allowance to a member of the Armed Forces who has obtained insurance coverage under the Servicemembers' Group Life Insurance program for each month during which such member: (1) served in an area for which special combat zone pay is authorized; (2) underwent training for immediate deployment to a combat zone; (3) underwent outprocessing immediately following return from a combat zone; (4) was in transit to or from a combat zone; (5) was hospitalized as a result of an injury, illness, or condition incurred or aggravated in a combat zone; or (6) was serving in pay grades E-1 through E-4. Makes the amount of such allowance the same amount as the pay deduction for such insurance coverage.</p> <p>Requires the Secretary concerned to notify eligible individuals of the availability of such allowance.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Ruben Estrella-Soto Act of 2005</title>
